name: Government shutdown
summary: With just three weeks before a potential government shutdown, Congress faces intense pressure to avoid a funding lapse. The House Republicans have proposed a bill to prevent the shutdown, but Senate Democrats have criticized it as a waste of time. The government shutdown looms as a major threat as Congress struggles to reach a funding deal, leaving many concerned about the potential fallout of a pre-election shutdown. House Republicans have privately expressed worries about the political consequences of a shutdown, while some lawmakers fear stumbling into a pre-election shutdown. The situation remains uncertain as Congress attempts to address the looming funding deadline.

name: James Earl Jones
summary: Legendary actor James Earl Jones, renowned for his iconic voice as Darth Vader and Mufasa in "Star Wars" and "The Lion King," respectively, has passed away at the age of 93. Throughout his illustrious career, Jones left an indelible mark on stage and screen, embodying memorable characters such as Avery in "The Great White Hope" and Terrance Mann in "Field of Dreams." His deep, resonant voice also lent its power to numerous narrations, including the iconic "This is CNN" for the cable news network. The news of Jones's passing has sparked an outpouring of tributes from fans and fellow actors, who celebrated his extraordinary talent and contribution to the world of entertainment.

name: Gmail
summary: Google has announced that it will be deleting inactive Gmail accounts, prompting users to take action to protect their accounts. name: Trabuco Canyon fire
summary: In Trabuco Canyon, Orange County, the Airport Fire has surged in size, prompting mandatory evacuation orders. The blaze, believed to have been ignited by public works equipment, has spread rapidly, threatening homes and forcing the evacuation of nearby residents. Three people have been injured, while over 300 acres have already been consumed by the flames. The Washington Post lists it among the active wildfires burning across California, Nevada, and Oregon. The Desert Sun reports that the fire is likely related to Orange County workers, while Newsweek provides a map showing the proximity of the wildfire to the airport. Both KTLA Los Angeles and NBC Los Angeles emphasize the evacuation orders, with NBC highlighting the explosion in the fire's size. The Los Angeles Times describes the fire as fast-moving and dangerous, while the OCRegister shares photographs of the ongoing blaze. The Daily Breeze reports on the 300-acre size of the fire, which is forcing nearby residents to flee. LAist similarly emphasizes the evacuations sparked by the Airport Fire.

name: Wheel of Fortune
summary: Ryan Seacrest has officially taken over as host of the iconic game show "Wheel of Fortune," alongside long-time co-host Vanna White. In his debut episode, Seacrest acknowledged the legendary status of Pat Sajak, the show's previous host, expressing his admiration for Sajak's immense impact on the show. Despite Seacrest's presence, the show's format and overall style remain familiar, preserving the beloved traditions that have made "Wheel of Fortune" a household name for decades. Nevertheless, Seacrest has promised to introduce some fresh elements and "souped-up" prizes to keep the show current and engaging for viewers. The reception to Seacrest's debut has been mixed, with some fans embracing the change and others expressing a sense of nostalgia for Sajak's presence.
